HEADWORD: Otozoum
<hw>O`to*zo"um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/, a fabled giant + <grk>zw^,on</grk> an animal.]</ety>
<fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>An extinct genus of huge vertebrates, probably
dinosaurs, known only from four-toed tracks in Triassic
sandstones.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

